              <span id="reviewTextContainer480577686" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15086043939714338083">A nice bridge book, lying between Moorcock&apos;s older swords &amp; sorcery and his newer, more philosophical novels. This provides some interesting orthagonal looks at his multiverse and also rather amusingly is a rejection of all things fantastic.</span>
  <span id="freeText15086043939714338083" style="display:none">A nice bridge book, lying between Moorcock's older swords &amp; sorcery and his newer, more philosophical novels. This provides some interesting orthagonal looks at his multiverse and also rather amusingly is a rejection of all things fantastic.</span>
