<div id="review_2804060771" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2804060771" />
    <a title="David" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70305200-david"><img alt="David" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1532355267p2/70305200.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2804060771?book_show_action=true">May 17, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="David" class="user" itemprop="url" name="David" href="/user/show/70305200-david">David</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780450049125" href="/book/show/1003324.The_War_Hound_And_The_World_s_Pain">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2804060771" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14137378888353127200">The phrase &apos;never judge a book by its cover&apos; could not be more appropriate for this book.<br/>Its setting in 17th century Europe gave a rich backdrop for our &apos;hero&apos; without wasting much time on unnecessary details. This book has swords and sorcery aplenty, but what makes it stand out is the protagonist&apos;s theological conclusions based on his experiences throughout the course of his journey.</span>
  <span id="freeText14137378888353127200" style="display:none">The phrase 'never judge a book by its cover' could not be more appropriate for this book.<br />Its setting in 17th century Europe gave a rich backdrop for our 'hero' without wasting much time on unnecessary details. This book has swords and sorcery aplenty, but what makes it stand out is the protagonist's theological conclusions based on his experiences throughout the course of his journey.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14137378888353127200" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
